accessibility.text: The camera follows the flight attendant through the rice paper doors and, with a clever transition, frames her stepping out from a traditional tent in the heart of Africa. Just as the protagonist steps out in the other location, she finishes her line, \"IN COMPLETELY NEW SITUATIONS.\"

We feel the vibrant energy through the resounding beat of drums, the rhythmic clapping of hands, and exclamations from the dancers. The flight attendant is still wearing her uniform but now accessorised with a beaded necklace. The camera briefly zooms in for a close-up on one of the tribal dancers' anklets — small, handcrafted bells attached to their ankles jingle with each movement. Here, our flight attendant joins the rhythmic dance.
